00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:02,800
Ever wondered why islands are biodiversity hotspots?

2
00:00:02,800 --> 00:00:07,200
Island biogeography studies how species thrive or struggle in isolated ecosystems.

3
00:00:07,200 --> 00:00:08,000
More species?

4
00:00:08,000 --> 00:00:08,800
Bigger islands!

5
00:00:08,800 --> 00:00:10,400
But, why is that?

6
00:00:10,400 --> 00:00:15,600
Research shows larger islands support greater diversity due to resources and habitat variety.

7
00:00:15,600 --> 00:00:20,400
Yet, isolation can lead to unique adaptations—think giant tortoises on the Galapagos!

